data.fullLabel:
DrugBank:
Ethinylestradiol
is a synthetic estrogenic
compound.[L11944] Use of
estrogens have a number of
effects on the body including
reduced bone density.[A191565]
Combined oral contraceptives
suppress ovulation by suppressing
gonadotrophic hormone,
thickening cervical mucus
to prevent the travel of sperm,
and preventing changes in
the endometrium required
for implantation of a fertilized
egg.[A191568,L11944] Ethinylestradiol
decreases luteinizing hormone,
decreasing vascularity
in the endometrium.[A191571]
It also increases sex hormone
binding globulin.[A191571]
data.value: Ethinylestradiol is a synthetic estrogenic compound.[L11944] Use of estrogens have a number of effects on the body including reduced bone density.[A191565] Combined oral contraceptives suppress ovulation by suppressing gonadotrophic hormone, thickening cervical mucus to prevent the travel of sperm, and preventing changes in the endometrium required for implantation of a fertilized egg.[A191568,L11944] Ethinylestradiol decreases luteinizing hormone, decreasing vascularity in the endometrium.[A191571] It also increases sex hormone binding globulin.[A191571]
